- Should I translate only the portion before a dot in fields like alternate_bases.AC and keep the suffix (AC, AF, n_alt_alleles, etc.) unchanged, resulting in Alternativbasen.AC, Alternativbasen.AF, etc.?
- For fields without a dot (e.g., reference_name, start_position), should I translate the entire term to natural German (e.g., Referenzname, Startposition)?
- How should I handle technical acronyms and region codes (AN, LCR, ASJ, etc.)—leave them as-is or translate to German equivalents (e.g., AN -> Anzahl der Allele)?
- Is it acceptable to produce translations that may combine terms into single words (e.g., Referenzname, Startposition) or should I prefer hyphenated/space-separated forms?
